Job Description of “Competitive Analysis Intern”
(Location: Intel China Software Center C Shanghai)
Responsibilities
 
 In this position, you will be responsible for benchmarking and competitive analysis for embedded systems that based on Intel XScale&amp;reg; processor.  Your responsibilities will include but not be limited to: 
- Responsible for workloads development for Intel XScale&amp;reg; based platform 
- Managing data acquisition from real devices 
- Responsible for system level performance and power analysis 
- Making conclusion and reporting out 
 
Qualifications
You must possess a Bachelor of Science degree or above in Electrical Engineering, Computer Science or equivalent. Additional qualifications include: 
- Strong ASM/C/C++ programming and C-coding skills 
- Knowledge of embedded systems 
- Experience in Multimedia processing, 2D/3D graphics and Java* programming 
- Experience in Supplier Quality Assurance (SQA) 
- Knowledge of embedded operating system (OS) architecture 
- Knowledge of ARM* (or other microprocessor) architecture 
- Excellent communication skills 
- Fluent English read/write/speak 
- Experience with Linux* and WinCE* OS would be an added advantage 
- Knowledge of hardware (HW) and software (SW) I/F would be an added advantage 
- Knowledge in hardware would be an added advantage
